# =============================================================================
# nullprobe — environment variables
# =============================================================================
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values for the vars you need.
# `.env.local` is gitignored; never commit secrets.
#
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# Loading:
#   - `.env.local` is read by nullprobe's runtime (Tavily search in
#     `nullprobe update`).
#   - MCP servers configured in `.mcp.json` / `.cursor/mcp.json` /
#     `.agent/mcp_config.json` / `.gemini/settings.json` substitute
#     `${VAR}` references from your *shell* environment, NOT from `.env.local`.
#     Export the MCP-facing vars in your shell rc (e.g. `~/.zshrc`) or via
#     your AI tool's env-injection mechanism.
#
# All variables here are OPTIONAL — nullprobe runs without any of them, but
# specific features degrade gracefully when their key is absent.
# =============================================================================


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# nullprobe CLI — runtime (read from `.env.local`)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Tavily web-search backend for `nullprobe update`.
# Without it, the Tavily branch prints setup instructions and exits cleanly.
# Sign up: https://app.tavily.com  →  Settings → API keys
# Format: tvly-<random>
TAVILY_API_KEY=

# GitHub API token for `nullprobe update` GitHub-search backend.
# Without it, unauthenticated requests work but are capped at 60/hour.
# With a token, the limit jumps to 5,000/hour.
# Create: https://github.com/settings/tokens  (scope: `public_repo` is enough)
GITHUB_TOKEN=


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MCP servers — dev sessions (export in your shell, NOT in `.env.local`)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are referenced as `${VAR}` from the repo's MCP configs and consumed
# by the AI tool launching the MCP server. They are listed here for discovery
# only — putting them in `.env.local` will NOT make MCP servers see them.
#
# To make them effective, add to your shell rc:
#   export CONTEXT7_API_KEY=...
#   export GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=...

# context7 MCP — up-to-date library docs.
# Sign up: https://context7.com  →  Dashboard → API key
CONTEXT7_API_KEY=

# GitHub MCP server — repo / issue / PR access from the AI.
# Can be the same value as `GITHUB_TOKEN` above, but kept separate because
# the official MCP server reads this exact variable name.
# Create: https://github.com/settings/tokens  (scopes per your needs:
#   `repo` for private repos, `read:org` for org metadata, etc.)
GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=
